Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Stennen L Jackson in court with Attorney Michael S. Holzman.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel, Charice M., and defendant.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  36  months  with 7 days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  18  months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  18  months.  
COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of  30  months.
Probation can be terminated/discharged by the probation agent after 24 months if probation is successfully completed.

Court finds defendant is  NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and  is  NOT  eligible for the Substance abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-  Serve 6 months in the House of Correction with Huber privileges for employment.  Condition time to commence no later than 5:00 p.m. on February 18, 2016
-  Mental Health evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment
-  Take all prescribed medication
-  AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment
-  Full-time employment or part-time employment and school or full-time school
-  No Contact Order with Kevin K.   AND/OR   Julie K.
-  Pay Restitution during the term of probation.  Restitution to be paid before costs, fees, assessments and surcharges.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  Restitution amount to be determined at restitution hearing.
-  No Contact with the co-actors Holley and Powell
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of probation.  Costs, fees, assessments and surcharges to be paid after restitution has been satisfied.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-  Mental Health evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment
-  Take all prescribed medication
-  AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment
-  Full-time employment or part-time employment and school or full-time school
-  No Contact Order with Kevin K.   AND/OR   Julie K.
-  Pay Restitution during the term of extended supervision.  Restitution to be paid before costs, fees, assessments and surcharges.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  Restitution amount to be determined at restitution hearing.
-  No Contact with the co-actors Holley and Powell
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of extended supervision.  Costs, fees, assessments and surcharges to be paid after restitution has been satisfied.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis (if not already done so)
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Pretrial Incarceration Credit and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
